x4freetext: Pulsed electron beam of 100 MeV on
depleted U target. Pulse duration 1 ns. Gamma flash is
generated via bremsstrahlung. Neutrons are produced
Collimated to 6.1 cm diameter at sample position.
Neutron flux at sample position is of order
GAINS detection system(Gamma Array for Inelastic
Neutron Scattering) consists of eight HPGe detectors
(100% relative efficiency), placed at 110 and 150 deg
with respect to the neutron beam. Distance between the
center of the sample and the front side of each
detector is of the order of 15 cm. Read-out by four
DC440 Acquiris digitizers. Typical energy resolution of
the large HPGe detectors read-out by the digitized
acquisition if of the order of 2.5 keV (FWHM) and the
time resolution is of the order of 8 ns.
Efficiency of the HPGe detectors is experimentally
determined using a calibrated Eu-152 source followed by
the reproduction of the values using a detailed Monte
Neutron beam is monitored using a 235U fission
chamber. Precise determination of the absolute
efficiency of the fission chamber is described in
